##Mask "heart" melt spurt cloth is so scarce, why doesn't the manufacturer take advantage of the production line, expand capacity?

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Visual China

REPORTER: Pang Keung

“

The supply cycle of melt blown cloth equipment is longer, and the cross-border production is more difficult, demanding and risky.

”

“

The supply cycle of melt blown cloth equipment is longer, and the cross-border production is more difficult, demanding and risky.

”

"everything is easy to say except the melt-blown cloth, " says one manufacturer in a supply-sharing exchange group for masks.

The group has gathered more than 100 mask industry upstream and downstream related manufacturers. They communicate in groups about masks. Although the price of ear band, nose bar and other materials is also rising, the supply is not in short supply.

It is a key ingredient in the mask industry -- a highly lucrative seller's market.

Medical N95 mask with melt-blown cloth, the current price generally came to 200,000 yuan per ton, compared with the initial price of the epidemic, more than 10 times.

"Medical N95 mask melt spurt cloth, only 1 ton, there is a need to contact quickly, " a manufacturer in the group sent a message. At the same time, he also reminded other businesses, pay attention to the purchase of meltblown cloth is in line with medical standards, beware of being deceived.

He said that because do not know the industry information, and anxious to obtain the source of goods, before many manufacturers have bought high-priced medical mask production standards of meltblown cloth, bear hundreds of thousands of yuan in vain losses.

With the rapid launch of mask production lines across the country, mask production in the near future there is an increase in express delivery. As of February 22, the daily production of face masks reached 54.77 million units, a 2.8 fold increase from February 1, and 570 million units have been produced in the past 20 days, according to the latest figures from the National Development and Reform Commission. But still many netizens said that they can not buy a mask.

Upstream meltblown fabric supply bottlenecks have become an important factor limiting mask production, and this gap is still widening.

In the huge demand stimulus, petrochina, Sinopec, Foxconn, SAIC-GM-Wuling Automobile, BYD Company and many other manufacturers have crossed the border to produce masks, petrochemical enterprises have also increased the supply of raw materials upstream polypropylene.

But why rare new MA melt spurt cloth production line or expansion of the news?

According to the interface reporters understand that this is mainly limited by the production equipment delivery cycle, high technical requirements for personnel operation and other reasons, meltblown cloth production capacity is difficult to quickly increase in a short time.

Meltblown cloth, full name meltblown nonwovens, is the key material that brings virus to filter function for mask. It has the electrostatic ultra-fine fiber, in addition to blocking larger dust particles, but also through the surface of the electrostatic charge will be fine dust, bacteria and viruses.

Medical masks generally adopt multi-layer structure, short for SMS structure: Inside and outside is single layer spunbonded layer (s) , middle is single layer or multi-layer meltblown layer (m) , meltblown cloth is the best material of meltblown layer.

Meltblown cloth is a kind of non-woven fabric. Nonwovens, also known as Nonwovens, are made of oriented or random fibers with no warp or weft threads, named for their appearance and certain properties similar to those of textile fabrics.

Non-woven fabrics have many processes, such as spunbonded, melt-blown, hot-rolled, spunlaced and so on. Among them, the melt-blown method made of non-woven fabric, known as the melt-blown non-woven fabric.

Melt-blown process refers to the spinning process in which a freshly extruded polymer melt is rapidly solidified by means of a high-speed hot air flow. MELTBLOWN nonwovens fiber is thinner, larger surface area, with better filtration, shielding, insulation and oil absorption, these are other processes produced by non-woven fabrics can not be compared.

Therefore, the meltblown cloth is widely used, in addition to the production of medical and industrial masks, it can also be used in many fields, such as heat preservation material, filter material, medical and sanitary material, oil absorption material, wiping cloth, battery separator and even sound insulation material.

Domestic production can produce meltblown cloth large manufacturers are not many, the industry as a whole presents a small and scattered situation. The industry has long been underwhelming in its lack of attention.

According to public information, at present, the domestic meltblown cloth production enterprises include Shandong Junfu non-woven Fabric Co. , Ltd. (Shandong Junfu) , Tianjin teda Clean Materials Co. , Ltd. (Tianjin Teda) , Xinlong Holding (Group) Co. , Ltd. . Among them, Shandong Junfu and Tianjin teda's meltblown cloth daily output of more than 10 tons.

In addition, there are a large number of small non-woven fabric manufacturers in Shandong, Guangdong, Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Tianjin and other provinces and cities, each daily output of about a ton.

The principle of meltblown cloth production is clear, but the actual production process is more complex, involving many disciplines such as polymer science, fluid mechanics, airflow, spinning science, etc. , the key is to obtain a complete set of meltblown cloth production equipment.

Zhejiang, a meltblown cloth production equipment suppliers also told interface reporters that after the Spring Festival, the industry focus from the mask machine to meltblown cloth, now focused on meltblown cloth production equipment.

There are not many factories in China that provide complete sets of production equipment and key parts of meltblown cloth. Mainly including the China Hengtian Group under the Grand Research Institute Co. , Ltd. , China Textile Machinery (Group) Co. , Ltd. under the Shaoyang Textile Machinery Co. , Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Shaoyang Textile Machinery) , Wenzhou Chaolong Textile Machinery Co. , Ltd. .

The major international manufacturers involved in meltblown production sets are: Kasen, Enka, Nippon Nozzle and Oerlikon Neumag.

At present, the production equipment of melt-blown cloth has been made in China, but the production of core parts, such as spinneret and Spinneret, still has a big gap with foreign manufacturers.

A person in charge of a meltblown cloth production enterprise in Jiangsu told an interface reporter that unlike the mask machine, which is low-cost and easy to operate, the price of meltblown cloth production equipment is generally more than one million yuan, and also needs to carry on the specialized training to the staff, the industry threshold is high.

"Some foreign manufacturers have a supply cycle of up to eight months, domestic manufacturers have more than six months, and key parts and components are dependent on imports. If the production line of Meltzer spray is truly introduced, perhaps the peak demand brought about by the epidemic has already passed, " said the person in charge.

Such concerns have discouraged many investors from entering the sector. The supply of the above-mentioned equipment for meltblown cloth production in Zhejiang also told the interface reporter that the meltblown cloth market is not big at all. Once the epidemic has passed, the competitive pressure of meltblown cloth producers will be very huge, similar to the SARS period, more than half of the entrants ended up losing money.

"This is too risky, " the source said, "even if domestic components are used, the overall delivery time will be more than three months. It is difficult for domestic equipment to maintain stable product quality for a long time, and the quality of the meltblown cloth is also the key to the quality of medical masks. "

Shaoyang textile machinery is an important meltblown cloth production equipment suppliers. The head of sales of the company told the interface reporter that the price of the company's ordinary fusible cloth production equipment is over 5 million yuan, the delivery cycle is about 4-5 months, and the price of the fusible cloth production equipment with larger width is higher, delivery Cycle Up to 7-8 months, plus 1-2 months of installation and commissioning time, the overall procurement and installation time of nearly 10 months.

"products such as dies and fans can be produced domestically, but the Spinneret, a key piece of equipment, needs to be imported from Enka, which limits our delivery time, " the head of sales said, "In addition to the equipment supply problem, the meltblown cloth production equipment is also more demanding for the operation of the staff, and the mask machine production line requirements are completely different. "

Sinopec announced on February 25 that it will invest about 200 million yuan to build meltblown and non-woven fabric production lines in Yan Mountains petrochemical and Yizheng Chemical Fiber to address the shortage of the core raw materials for masks. Among them, Yan Mountains is aiming to start production in part on March 8.
